lead_paragraph: The Big Ten this week embarks on its first nine-game conference schedule, rekindling the debate whether all Power Five conferences should play the same number of league games in the era of the College Football Playoff.

headline.print_headline: Riley: Power 5 Teams Should Play Same Number of League Games
